{"questionId":"14414972","questionHtml":"<p>Show that this post is safe for children. Justify your answer.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to find the maximum angle measure of the post using trigonometry&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>e.g. <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>10</mn><mrow><mn>10</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7061</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; <strong>OR</strong>&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>82393</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mo>(</mo><mn>90</mn><mo>°</mo><mo>)</mo></mrow><mrow><mn>10</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7061</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Accept an inequality.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>)</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>20</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mo>°</mo><mo>)</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>20</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9265</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>(</mo><mo>°</mo><mo>)</mo><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong> A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>and hence the post is safe&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Use of radians gives an answer of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>365</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>365237</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>)</mo></math>; award at most <em><strong>(M1)A0</strong></em> since this value cannot be directly compared to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>22</mn><mo>°</mo></math>.</p>\n<p>Award at most <em><strong>(M1)A0</strong></em> for an angle calculated using their lower bound from part (b).</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to find the longest slant height for angle to be a maximum of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>22</mn><mo>°</mo></math> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>e.g. <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mo>(</mo><mn>22</mn><mo>°</mo><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>10</mn><mi>x</mi></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7853</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>)</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7061</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7853</mn><mo>…</mo></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>and hence the post is safe&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong><em>AG</em></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> A comparison to their upper bound from part (b) is required for <em><strong>A1</strong></em> to be awarded. Use of radians gives an unreasonable answer of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0003</mn><mo>…</mo></math>; award at most <em><strong>(M1)A0</strong></em>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"14414972","referenceCode":"23M.1.SL.TZ1.11c","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Show that this post is safe for children. Justify your answer.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.2—2d and 3d trig","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.3—Angles of elevation and depression","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.6—Approximating and estimating"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}